---
import SiteLayout from '../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
---

<SiteLayout title="Getting Started | Curl Crypto" description="Setup guide for the Curl Crypto plugin.">
  <article class="doc-article">
    <p class="eyebrow">Getting Started</p>
    <h1>Install the local CLI and keep service-specific details in local config.</h1>
    <p>
      The plugin is designed around a local command surface. The public repository stays generic; the sensitive
      service settings live in a private config file on each machine.
    </p>

    <h2>Install</h2>
    <pre><code>command -v curl-crypto >/dev/null || npm install -g github:leeguooooo/curl-crypto-plugin</code></pre>

    <h2>Verify</h2>
    <pre><code>curl-crypto self-test</code></pre>

    <h2>Initialize local config</h2>
    <pre><code>curl-crypto config init</code></pre>

    <h2>First decrypt example</h2>
    <pre><code>curl-crypto decrypt-curl --curl-file request.curl</code></pre>

    <h2>When to pass values explicitly</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Pass <code>--key</code> when the request does not expose a key through configured headers.</li>
      <li>Pass <code>--key-suffix</code> when the request needs a second key fragment.</li>
      <li>Use <code>--config</code> or <code>CURL_CRYPTO_CONFIG</code> when the private config file lives outside the default path.</li>
    </ul>
  </article>
</SiteLayout>
